unifi:IAM/group:Group.description:
`unifi.IAM.Group` manages a user group (called "client group" in the UI), which can be used to limit bandwidth for groups of users.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as unifi from "@pulumi/unifi";

const wifi = new unifi.IAM.Group("wifi", {
    qosRateMaxDown: 2000, // 2mbps
    qosRateMaxUp: 10, // 10kbps
});
```
{{% /example %}}
{{% /examples %}}

## Import

# import using the ID

```sh
 $ pulumi import unifi:IAM/group:Group wifi 5fe6261995fe130013456a36
```

unifi:index/site:Site.description:
`unifi.Site` manages Unifi sites

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as unifi from "@pulumi/unifi";

const mysite = new unifi.Site("mysite", {
    description: "mysite",
});
```
{{% /example %}}
{{% /examples %}}

## Import

# import using the API/UI ID

```sh
 $ pulumi import unifi:index/site:Site mysite 5fe6261995fe130013456a36
```

 # import using the name (short ID)

```sh
 $ pulumi import unifi:index/site:Site mysite vq98kwez
```

unifi:IAM/getUser:getUser.description:
`unifi.IAM.User` retrieves properties of a user (or "client" in the UI) of the network by MAC address.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as unifi from "@pulumi/unifi";

const client = pulumi.output(unifi.IAM.getUser({
    mac: "01:23:45:67:89:ab",
}));
```
{{% /example %}}
{{% /examples %}}

